stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    state "Waiting for user message" as Waiting
    state "Ready to stream" as Ready
    state "LLM streaming" as Streaming
    state "Interrupting stream" as InterruptingStream
    state "Stream interrupted\n(partial response retained)" as StreamInterrupted
    state "Stream failed\n(partial response retained)" as StreamFailed
    state "Has tool calls" as HasTools
    state "Waiting for tool consent" as NeedConsent
    state "Tool calls running" as RunningTools
    state "Interrupting tool execution" as InterruptingTools
    state "Closed" as Closed

    [*] --> Waiting

    Waiting --> Ready: SendMessage
    StreamInterrupted --> Streaming: SendMessage\n(continue partial response)
    StreamFailed --> Streaming: SendMessage\n(continue partial response)

    Ready --> Streaming: create_stream

    Streaming --> Waiting: stream completes\n(no tool calls)
    Streaming --> HasTools: stream completes\n(tool calls returned)
    Streaming --> StreamFailed: provider error
    Streaming --> InterruptingStream: Interrupt\n(cancel stream)

    InterruptingStream --> StreamInterrupted: stream returns Interrupted
    InterruptingStream --> Streaming: pending SendMessage exists\n(continue partial response)

    HasTools --> RunningTools: all calls auto-approved
    HasTools --> NeedConsent: at least one call\nneeds consent

    NeedConsent --> NeedConsent: ToolDecision\n(more decisions pending)
    NeedConsent --> RunningTools: all decisions recorded\nstart ToolExecution

    RunningTools --> Streaming: tool batch completes\nappend tool results, create_stream
    RunningTools --> InterruptingTools: Interrupt\n(cancel tool execution)
    InterruptingTools --> Streaming: interrupted calls resolved\nappend results, create_stream

    Waiting --> Closed: Stop
    Ready --> Closed: Stop
    Streaming --> Closed: Stop\n(session loop exits)
    InterruptingStream --> Closed: Stop\n(session loop exits)
    StreamInterrupted --> Closed: Stop
    StreamFailed --> Closed: Stop
    HasTools --> Closed: Stop
    NeedConsent --> Closed: Stop
    RunningTools --> Closed: Stop\n(session loop exits)
    InterruptingTools --> Closed: Stop\n(session loop exits)

    note right of Waiting
        The session loop owns the current state and
        serializes external commands with internal
        stream/tool completion messages.
    end note

    note right of InterruptingStream
        A SendMessage received while cancellation
        is draining is retained as pending_message.
    end note

    note right of NeedConsent
        ToolDecision starts execution directly after
        every non-auto-approved call is decided.
    end note

    note right of Ready
        ReadyToStream is a transient typed-agent state;
        the harness stores Streaming after spawning the future.
    end note
